- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the construction of a distributed spanning tree on an unknown graph environment, which involves the use of algorithms and data structures. 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems): The paper focuses on the behavior and interactions of multiple mobile agents in a distributed setting. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper deals with the construction of a network (spanning tree) in an unknown graph environment, which is a common topic in social and information networks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the behavior and control of a system of mobile agents in a distributed setting. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper involves the study of the behavior and interactions of multiple agents, which is a common topic in game theory.
